  "prompt": "What hotel in Dharamshala Hill-station would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "In Dharamshala, as in many other hill stations in India, the legal framework allows unmarried couples to stay together in hotels, provided they can present valid identification. However, the reality can sometimes be complicated due to societal attitudes or misconceptions among hotel staff.\n\nHere are some tips and suggestions for finding a safe and welcoming hotel for unmarried couples in Dharamshala:\n\n### Hotels Known to Be Couple-Friendly:\n1. **Hotel Tibet**  \n   - Known for its welcoming staff and professional service, this hotel is a good option for couples.  \n   - It\u2019s centrally located and has a good reputation for discretion and hospitality.  \n\n2. **Fortune Park Moksha**  \n   - A well-known chain hotel that adheres to professional standards and respects guest privacy.  \n   - Ideal for those looking for a more upscale and secure stay.  \n\n3. **The Orchard Greens Resort & Spa**  \n   - Offers a peaceful and private environment, suitable for couples.  \n   - Staff are trained to respect guest privacy.  \n\n4. **Sterling Dharamshala**  \n   - Part of a reputable chain, this hotel ensures a hassle-free experience for all guests.  \n\n### General Tips for Booking:\n- **Book in Advance**: Use trusted platforms like **MakeMyTrip**, **Booking.com**, or **OYO** and look for hotels labeled as \"couple-friendly\" or \"unmarried couple-friendly.\"  \n- **Check Reviews**: Look for recent reviews from unmarried couples to ensure the hotel is welcoming and safe.  \n- **Confirm with the Hotel**: Call the hotel directly before booking to confirm their policies for unmarried couples.  \n- **Carry Valid ID**: Both partners should carry valid government-issued IDs (Aadhaar, Passport, etc.) for check-in.  \n- **Avoid Budget or Local Guesthouses**: These may have stricter policies or less professionalism regarding unmarried couples.  \n\n### Legal Rights:\n- The **Supreme Court of India** has upheld the right of unmarried couples to live together, and hotels are legally bound to respect this.  \n- If you face any harassment, you can call the police or report the issue to hotel management.  \n\nBy choosing a reputed hotel and communicating clearly, you should be able to enjoy a safe and hassle-free stay in Dharamshala.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
